-- Citigroup Asia Pacific banking exec Faruqui leaving -memo
-- 
-- Tue May 13, 2014 10:44AM EDT
-- None



May 13 (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc's <C.N> head of Corporate and Investment Banking for Asia Pacific, Farhan Faruqui, is leaving the company, according to an internal memo.

Faruqui, a 23-year veteran of the company, is departing for "the next stage of his career," according to the memo, which was seen by Reuters. He held his current job for five years.